SCROLLING.Definition: to move text or pictures up or down on a screen

COMMITMENT.Definition: a promise or firm decision to do something

INSPIRATION.Definition: a force or influence that makes someone want to do something

SURGE.Definition: a sudden and great increase, typically a temporary one

REGULAR BASIS.Definition: quite often or in a consistent, regular manner

IN TROUBLE.Definition: a situation in which you experience problems

FUNNY ENOUGH.Definition: used to express that something is surprising; oddly enough

TEMPTED.Definition: a strong urge or desire to do something

NEGLECT.Definition: to not give enough care or attention

SEEK.Definition: to try to find or get something

FUELED.Definition: to increase or make something stronger

THE KEY.Definition: the best or only way to achieve something

MEMORIZE.Definition: to learn something and remember it exactly

TOOL.Definition: something that helps you to do a particular activity

STUCK.Definition: unable to move from a place; or unable to change a situation

OTHERWISE.Definition: used to express what the result is going to be if something do not happen

BRIGHT.Definition: the advantages or good characteristics of a situation

DETERMINE.Definition: to control or influence something directly

STEPPING OUTSIDE OF YOUR COMFORT ZONE.Definition: doing things that you don't feel comfortable with doing

EFFORT.Definition: a determined attempt to do something

CLICHE.Definition: an idea that has been overused to the point of seeming ineffective or meaningless

PROGRESS.Definition: movement to an improved or more developed state

GETTING RID OF.Definition: to remove something that you do not want any longer

JUDGING.Definition: form an opinion or conclusion about something; criticize someone's behavior

STAGNATION.Definition: lack of activity, growth, or development

KICK IN THE ASS.Definition: a rebuke that is intended to or serves to motivate one to improve

HOLD YOURSELF ACCOUNTABLE.Definition: being responsible for something; being answerable for your actions

SELF-AWARENESS.Definition: having conscious knowledge of one's own character and feelings

RARE.Definition: not common or frequent; very unusual

INDEED.Definition: used to emphasize the truth of something

CONSEQUENCES.Definition: a result or effect of an action or situation

GODDAMN.Definition: used to express any strong feeling, especially of annoyance, anger or surprise

RELY ON.Definition: to trust in or depend on

LIFT WEIGHTS.Definition: to exercise by moving heavy objects from a lower to a higher position

CONSISTENTLY.Definition: in a way that does not change and continues for a period of time
